<h2> Contact information </h2>
<p>
 If you need help, try asking for help in the following places:

 <ul>
   <li> On IRC. The <code>#debian</code> channel on <code>irc.debian.org</code>.
        Someone is always on-line and happy to share information and help you
        with your problem. </li>
   <li> Mailing Lists (see above)</li>
   <li> Usenet Newsgroups (see above)</li>
   <li> Finally, if all else fails, you can send e-mail to the Debian/PowerPC
        port coordinator, at <a href="mailto:koptein@debian.org">Hartmut Koptein
        &lt;koptein@debian.org&gt;</a>.</li>
 </ul>

<h2> Debian GNU/Linux installation on PowerPC machines </h2>
<p>
 Installing Debian/PowerPC is not as simple as installing Debian for some
 other systems, because of the variety of systems using the PowerPC
 microprocessor. Check our <a href="inst/install">Installation</a> pages
 for specific information about installing Debian/PowerPC on your system.
</p>

